{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"37aa6928-0ee4-5417-9f26-36fc668e7dad","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-vagrant\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-vagrant\" aria-label=\"awesome vagrant permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Vagrant</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a> <a href=\"https://gitter.im/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant?utm_source=badge&#x26;utm_medium=badge&#x26;utm_campaign=pr-badge\"><img src=\"https://badges.gitter.im/Join%20Chat.svg\" alt=\"Gitter\"></a> <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant\"><img src=\"https://api.travis-ci.org/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"Build Status\"></a></p>\n<p>A curated list of awesome Vagrant resources, plugins, tutorials and other nice things.</p>\n<h2 id=\"official-resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#official-resources\" aria-label=\"official resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Official resources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.vagrantup.com/\">Vagrant site</a> - installation instruction, official manuals and docs.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hashicorp/vagrant\">GitHub repo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hashicorp/vagrant\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21.9k</span></span></a> - source code, issues discussion and collaboration.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"boxes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#boxes\" aria-label=\"boxes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Boxes</h2>\n<p><em>Where to find OS boxes ?</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.vagrantbox.es/\">Vagrantbox.es</a> - the biggest list of all available boxes, maintained by community via GitHub pull requests.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://app.vagrantup.com/boxes/search\">Vagrant Cloud</a> - config share, boxes distribution and discovery (also premium features of private collaboration and sharing).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/vagrant/\">Cloud Images Ubuntu.com</a> - \"clean\" official Ubuntu cloud images.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/chef/bento#current-baseboxes\">Baseboxes from Opscode</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/chef/bento#current-baseboxes\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.7k</span></span></a> - CentOS, Fedora, Debian, FreeBSD, Ubuntu.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://puppet-vagrant-boxes.puppetlabs.com/\">Puppet Labs Vagrant Boxes</a> - these boxes are provided to be used by various Puppet projects.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloudsmith.io\">Cloudsmith</a> - A fully managed package management SaaS with support for Vagrant repositories (and many others).</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"provisioning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#provisioning\" aria-label=\"provisioning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Provisioning</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/provisioning\">All available build in provisioning providers</a> - official doc.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://fideloper.github.io/Vaprobash/index.html\">Vaprobash</a> - Vagrant Provisioning Bash Scripts.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"notable-plugins\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#notable-plugins\" aria-label=\"notable plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Notable plugins</h2>\n<p><em>You can install these modules by this command <code class=\"language-text\">vagrant plugin install MODULE-NAME</code></em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hashicorp/vagrant/wiki/Available-Vagrant-Plugins\">List of available Vagrant plugins from GitHub wiki</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dotless-de/vagrant-vbguest\">vagrant-vbguest</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dotless-de/vagrant-vbguest\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.8k</span></span></a> - autoupdate VirtualBox guest additions (according to VB version).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cogitatio/vagrant-hostsupdater\">vagrant-hostsupdater</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cogitatio/vagrant-hostsupdater\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.2k</span></span></a> - adds an entry to your /etc/hosts file on the host system.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://fgrehm.viewdocs.io/vagrant-cachier/\">vagrant-cachier</a> - share a common package (apt-get, npm, etc.) cache among similar VM instances.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/phinze/vagrant-host-shell\">vagrant-host-shell</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/phinze/vagrant-host-shell\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">115</span></span></a> - a vagrant provisioner to run commands on the host when a VM boots.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jaugustin/vagrant-ansible-local\">vagrant-ansible-local</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jaugustin/vagrant-ansible-local\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">65</span></span></a>  allow provisioning your VM with ansible playbooks directly from the guest VM.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jedi4ever/sahara\">sahara</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jedi4ever/sahara\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">729</span></span></a> - easy manage VM state (commit/rollback while experimenting with software stack).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-vagrant-registration\">vagrant-registration</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-vagrant-registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">49</span></span></a> - add \"register\" and \"unregister\" capabilities to Vagrant guests for updates on systems with a subscription model(like Red Hat Enterprise Linux).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/vagrant-service-manager\">vagrant-service-manager</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/vagrant-service-manager\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">18</span></span></a> - enable easier access to the features and services provided by the <a href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-atomic-developer-bundle\">Atomic Developer Bundle (ADB)</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-atomic-developer-bundle\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">81</span></span></a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/invernizzi/vagrant-scp\">vagrant-scp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/invernizzi/vagrant-scp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">277</span></span></a> - Copy files to a Vagrant VM via SCP.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"helpers--tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#helpers--tools\" aria-label=\"helpers  tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Helpers / Tools</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.packer.io/\">Packer</a> - a tool for creating identical machine images for multiple platforms from a single source configuration. For fast infrastructure deployment with multi-provider portability.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thomvaill/tads-boilerplate\">T.A.D.S. boilerplate</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Thomvaill/tads-boilerplate\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">441</span></span></a> - boilerplate to create, develop and deploy a Docker Swarm environment, using Vagrant to reproduce production environment locally.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jedi4ever/veewee\">Veewee</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jedi4ever/veewee\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.3k</span></span></a> - a tool for easily (and repeatedly) building custom Vagrant base boxes, KVMs, and virtual machine images.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/wiki/Plugins#vagrant\">Vagrant plugin for ZSH shell</a> - auto-complete for commands, task names, box names and built-in documentation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MunGell/vgm\">CLI Vagrant Manager</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MunGell/vgm\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a> - simple command-line tool to manage multiple vagrant boxes</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"desktop-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#desktop-tools\" aria-label=\"desktop tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Desktop tools</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://vagrantmanager.com/\">Vagrant Manager</a> for OS X.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"web-services\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#web-services\" aria-label=\"web services permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Web services</h2>\n<p><em>To generate Vagrantfile with automated provisioning scripts.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://phansible.com/\">Phansible</a> - provides an easy to use interface that helps you generate Ansible Playbooks for PHP based projects.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://puphpet.com/\">PuPHPet</a> - a simple GUI to set up virtual machines for <s></s>PHP Web development.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://getprotobox.com/\">Protobox</a> - PuPHPet analog, but uses own installer with YAML configuration format to control everything that is installed on the virtual machine.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://rove.io/\">Rove</a> - a service that allows you to pregenerate typical Vagrant builds.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"proxy-services\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#proxy-services\" aria-label=\"proxy services permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Proxy services</h2>\n<p><em>To proxy your local web server and make it publicly available over the internet.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/share/\">Vagrant share</a> - allows you to share your Vagrant environment with anyone in the world.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://nip.io\">nip.io</a> - a magic domain name that provides wildcard DNS</li>\n</ul>\n<p>for any IP address.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://ngrok.com/\">ngrok</a> - tool to create secure tunnels to expose a local server behind a NAT or firewall to the internet.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://serveo.net/\">serveo</a> - expose local servers to the internet, without installing any client!</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://proxylocal.com\">proxylocal.com</a> - proxy your local web-server and make it publicly available over the internet.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://localtunnel.github.io/www/\">localtunnel.me</a> - assign you a unique publicly accessible url that will proxy all requests to your locally running webserver.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://portmap.io/\">portmap.io</a> - OpenVPN based free port forwarding solution.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"tutorials\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tutorials\" aria-label=\"tutorials permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tutorials</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.thisprogrammingthing.com/2013/getting-started-with-vagrant/\">Getting Started With Vagrant</a> by This Programming Thing.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://stdout.in/en/post/getting_started_with_vagrant_automated_dev_servers_deploy_and_provisioning\">Getting started with Vagrant - automated dev servers deploy and provisioning.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://confluence.jetbrains.com/display/PhpStorm/Working+with+Advanced+Vagrant+features+in+PhpStorm\">Working with Advanced Vagrant features in PhpStorm.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scotch.io/tutorials/sharing-your-virtual-machine-on-the-web-with-vagrant-share\">Sharing Your Virtual Machine on the Web with Vagrant Share</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://hackr.io/tutorials/learn-vagrant\">Programming Community Curated Resources for Learning Vagrant</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://classpert.com/vagrant\">Vagrant Online Courses at Classpert</a> List of Vagrant Online Courses (free and paid)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Vagrant-Running-Virtualized-Development-Environments/dp/1449335837\">Vagrant: Up and Running</a> by Mitchell Hashimoto.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/vagrantcookbook\">Vagrant CookBook</a> by Erika Heidi.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Pro-Vagrant-Wlodzimierz-Gajda/dp/1484200748/\">Pro Vagrant</a> by by Wlodzimierz Gajda.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/9781849519182.do\">Creating Development Environments with Vagrant</a> / <a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/9781784397029.do\">2nd Edition</a> by Michael Peacock</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/9781784393748.do\">Vagrant Virtual Development Environment Cookbook</a> by Chad Thompson</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"popular-readymade-environments\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#popular-readymade-environments\" aria-label=\"popular readymade environments permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Popular readymade environments</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vagrantpress/vagrantpress\">Vagrantpress</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vagrantpress/vagrantpress\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">747</span></span></a> - development environment for creating and modifying WordPress sites.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Varying-Vagrant-Vagrants/VVV\">Varying Vagrant Vagrants</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Varying-Vagrant-Vagrants/VVV\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.5k</span></span></a> - An open source Vagrant configuration focused on WordPress development.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/joomlatools/joomlatools-vagrant\">Joomla-Vagrant</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/joomlatools/joomlatools-vagrant\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">142</span></span></a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.drupal.org/project/vdd\">VDD</a> - Vagrant Drupal Development.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.drupalvm.com/\">Drupal VM</a> - A VM for local Drupal development, built with Vagrant + Ansible</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/iJackUA/try-yii2\">Try Yii2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/iJackUA/try-yii2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">50</span></span></a> - try Yii2 with Vagrant VM + Ansible provisioning = Complete readymade virtual server playground.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bryannielsen/Laravel4-Vagrant\">Laravel4-Vagrant</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bryannielsen/Laravel4-Vagrant\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">495</span></span></a> - run Laravel 4 inside a Ubuntu 12.04 Vagrant Virtual Machine w/PHP 5.5.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openstack-ansible/openstack-ansible\">OpenStack on Ansible with Vagrant</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/openstack-ansible/openstack-ansible\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">217</span></span></a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://laravel.com/docs/master/homestead\">Laravel Homestead</a> - Official Vagrant Box for Laravel development, based on Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, PHP 7, Nginx, and multiple database platforms.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scotch.io/bar-talk/announcing-scotch-box-2-0-our-dead-simple-vagrant-lamp-stack-improved\">Scotch Box</a> - Simple Vagrant Box with <a href=\"https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAMP_%28software_bundle%29\">LAMP</a> stack, plus some useful extras, based on Ubuntu 14.04 LTS.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"license\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#license\" aria-label=\"license permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>License</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/\"><img src=\"https://licensebuttons.net/p/zero/1.0/88x31.png\" alt=\"CC0\"></a></p>\n<p>To the extent possible under law, <a href=\"http://stdout.in/\">Ievgen Kuzminov</a> has waived all copyright and related or neighboring rights to this work.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#awesome-vagrant\">Awesome Vagrant</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#official-resources\">Official resources</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#boxes\">Boxes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#provisioning\">Provisioning</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#notable-plugins\">Notable plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#helpers--tools\">Helpers / Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#desktop-tools\">Desktop tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#web-services\">Web services</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#proxy-services\">Proxy services</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#tutorials\">Tutorials</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#books\">Books</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#popular-readymade-environments\">Popular readymade environments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#license\">License</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"awesome-vagrant","value":"Awesome Vagrant","depth":1},{"id":"official-resources","value":"Official resources","depth":2},{"id":"boxes","value":"Boxes","depth":2},{"id":"provisioning","value":"Provisioning","depth":2}